description_for_model:
This plugin provides 2 main functionalities: 1. Provides APIs for getting the Google Cloud Projects list for the user, as well as getting the necessary access token that is used when getting the projects list. The whole flow is like this:
a. Get the IDP token for the user through the API GET /idptoken;
b. Call GET /gcpaccesstoken to get the Google Cloud access token, which will be passed as a param in the /gcpprojects call;
c. Call POST /gcpprojects with access_token to get the list of projects for the user.
 2. Provides APIs to query Bigquery with the given project id and dataset id. The whole flow is like this:
a. Get the IDP token for the user through the API GET /idptoken;
b. Call GET /gcpaccesstoken to get the Google Cloud access token, which will be passed as a param in the /gcpprojects call;
c. Call GET /bigquery with access_token to get the Bigquery dataset.
